reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee shop in Cornelius! I have always had amazing service and they’ve never made me a bad coffee. :)

reviews_data.review_text:

Cute atmosphere but coffee was only ok.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Good Morning Alexis... sorry to know we missed the mark in making your drinks the way you like them... we appreciate the feedback and are happy to make adjustments to give you the best drinks, food, and experience at Willow Wood.   We hope to see you again.

reviews_data.review_text: I've always enjoyed everything I've had here, great spot!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Sara:). Thank you for the stars!  We are so glad you know you enjoy your time at Willow Wood.

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing menu, amazing coffee, 10/10 service!

Great coffee & matcha tea. However, changing review since they got rid of my favorite breakfast item, the Breakfast Tortilla Bowl. It was by far the best item on menu. The service & atmosphere is still great though.

We recognize seating can be an issue, especially as the weather gets cooler and outdoor seating is not an option.  We are happy to join tables together to accommodate a group of 6-8 or even more depending on the time of day.  If you can call ahead we'll make every effort to seat your group  or join the tables when you get there depending on the time of day/crowd.  Thank you so much for your support and taking the time to give us the feedback:)

reviews_data.review_text: Had a great breakfast and the people were great!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Great Photo!  Love it:). Thank you for posting and thank you for the nice review.  Glad you enjoyed your time at Willow Wood :)

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee! Food was pretty good. The atmosphere is great for reading, socializing, chilling, or just grabbing a meal.

reviews_data.review_text: Highly recommend the Whitewater if you're looking for a unique coffee drink! And their breakfast sandwiches are super affordable for a quick breakfast.

reviews_data.review_text: I come here often for meetings with friends or industry professionals and I forget to take pictures. It is one of our favorite places to grab a cup of joe.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Karen.   We appreciate your consistent support and kindness in so many ways  ..  ☕️

reviews_data.review_text:

reviews_data.review_text:

reviews_data.review_text: Cozy place with attentive staff. The cappuccino was made perfectly on the first try – so delicious! Highly recommend for true coffee lovers.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Inna! Look forward to seeing you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: It is a undisputed fact that Willow Wood coffee is the best coffee in Cornelius. They are a breath of fresh air from the corporate coffee chains that pollute the local scene. Excellent atmosphere and a dedicated staff. The food is killer, too!

reviews_data.review_text: Great ambience, really good coffee and service with a smile! I needed a good  spot to catch up on some work this morning and I decided to stop in. The ambience was extremely comfortable and inviting just as you would expect for a Café. They had a very nice menu of drinks and a pastry selection that looked absolutely to die for. The coffee was hot, the Wi-Fi signal was strong, and the servers were extremely pleasant. I will definitely make this a regular spot when I’m in the area.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so glad you found us and had a great experience:)  We hope you'll resolve in 2025 to try every to-die-for pastry!  Worth it! Thank you for coming and for making us your coffee shop!  (P.S.  We like your prose: coffee was hot, and the Wi-fi strong:)

reviews_data.review_text: Best lattes in Cornelius
reviews_data.owner_answer: Best customers in Cornelius !  Thank you ❤️

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Tara!  So glad you enjoyed the Christmas Cookie Chai... Christmas in a cup!   Thank you for the kind words... it warms our hearts:)

reviews_data.review_text:
I've been there 2 times out of the many that I will be there.   The atmosphere of a coffee shop is important to me.  It can't be too fancy because you're not sipping tea, and you're not an aristocrat.  Know what I'm saying? This is the place for someone who loves coffee.

reviews_data.review_text: Came in didn't feel rushed, ordered our drinks which were fantastic  and they were brought to us by staff. Everyone was kind with smiles and polite. Definitely going back again always a good time and fair prices.

reviews_data.review_text: Nice little coffee shop. Service was excellent. WiFi worked. Cappuccino was excellent.

reviews_data.review_text: My favorite coffee shop in the Lake Norman area. Love their lattes (The Bluestone and Oh Wow! are my favorites). Prices are more economical than some other cafes in the area, which makes me come here more than the others (I'm tired of paying $7-8 for a latte at other cafes.) They also have good bfast and lunch options. My only critique is the lack of gluten-free bread, which is a pretty easy option for cafes to have these days (GF bread can be kept in a freezer or fridge for a long time without going bad.) I love the nice atmosphere with a chill, peaceful vibe. Great place to get some writing done. Thank you!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you SO much John ☕️ We appreciate you and your feedback.  Yes , you’re right. … we will stock gluten free bread in the future.    We appreciate your recognition that we strive to keep our prices as low as possible for our customers.    And we’re happy to know  you enjoy our specialty drinks and our shop 😊thanks again

reviews_data.review_text: Love the coffee and atmosphere!

reviews_data.review_text: Really excellent little shop. The staff are wonderfully nice and the atmosphere is really lovely. The food they have on menu is good and well made however the only criticism I have is that the menu is not very inclusive of dietary issues. They had some vegetarian options but no true dairy free/vegan options. I would give this place a full 5 stars if they added some dairy free or vegan pastries and menu items. Would make this place AWESOME!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello there Cole... thank you for the feedback... we have introduced avocado toast as a vegetarian option, available on gluten free bread.  Some dishes can be adapted and We will do everything we can to accommodate   dietary needs.    We have diligently sought gluten free from local bakeries who are not equipped to produce specialty baked goods like gluten free and vegetarian:(. But we're still pursuing options to provide that.  Thank you for your support and the time you took to provide meaningful feedback.

reviews_data.review_text: Lovely coffee house, delicious coffee and sandwiches. I’m giving 3 stars because this is the 3rd time I came here to to have  breakfast and coffee with a friend and had to take it to go because there was no place to eat. People with laptops taking up practically every table, one person with a laptop taking up one whole table. Owner needs to add more tables or somehow manage the existing ones so that people not drinking coffee can’t stop people who are actually there for a social reason have a place to drink theirs!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Lisa... we're so sorry you didn't have a place to sit to have your breakfast :(   We have encouraged single people with computers to sit at a table for two by putting signs on the booth tables.   Enforcing "consideration" among some customers is a precarious  position, but we are considering additional measures to try and manage it.   As you can imagine, adding seating is less of an option considering ADA compliance and general safety, fire laws, etc.  All that said, we appreciate you sticking with us (coming in your third time!), and please ask a barista to assist you with getting a table if it seems possible to ask someone to move  to a smaller table.    Thank you again .. we do appreciate you.

Been here a couple of times since they opened. I’m actually a tea drinker and it is nice to find a local business that offers loose leaf tea. So far, I have had their Morning Fog with oat milk and just a hot Masala Chai.
The service is friendly, the place is very clean and the ambiance is nice. Most tables have charging stations or outlets and the do offer wifi. They also have some outdoor seating for the beautiful weather.
They offer a wide selection of non-dairy milks which I appreciate.
My sister has had their coffee and she is a fan. Not bitter and they make it super hot just how she likes them.
Shopping center has parking though it may get a little tight during busy hours. Highly recommend.
